Others: The Togo national football team will be missing their starting goalkeeper, Jeffrey Agboloso, due to a surgery on his ankle. Agboloso, 24, plays for FC Balagne in France and was a key player in the team's previous qualification matches, starting as the goalkeeper against Liberia and Equatorial Guinea.

The absence of Agboloso is a significant blow to the team as they prepare to face Algeria on October 10, 2024. The Togo team is currently in Tunisia for preparation and will travel to Annaba, Algeria, today to face the Algerian team.
The article does not provide any information about the match itself, such as key events, new records, or post-match reflections.
